question: Rank the actors of the South Yorkshire region by number of projects
sql_query: select t2.institutions_name, count(distinct t1.project) from project_members as t1 join institutions t2 on t1.institution_id = t2.unics_id where t1.region_name='South Yorkshire' group by t2.institutions_name order by count(distinct t1.project) desc

question: Show the H2020 funding received by the region of Emilia-Romagna
sql_query: select sum(t1.ec_contribution) from project_members as t1 join projects as t2 on t1.project=t2.unics_id where t1.region_name='Emilia-Romagna' and t2.framework_program='H2020'

question: Show the title of the FP7 projects of the Comunidad de Madrid region
sql_query: select distinct t2.title from project_members as t1 join projects as t2 on t1.project=t2.unics_id where t1.region_name='Comunidad de Madrid' and t2.framework_program='FP7'

question: Show the topics of the H2020 projects with participation of the region with code ES43
sql_query: select distinct t3.title from project_members as t1 join project_topics as t2 on t2.project=t1.project join topics as t3 on t3.code=t2.topic join projects as t4 on t1.project=t4.unics_id where t1.region_code='ES43' and t4.framework_program='H2020'

question: Show the code and title of the H2020 programs in which the region of Toscana has participated
sql_query: select distinct t3.code, t3.title from project_members as t1 join project_programmes as t2 on t2.project=t1.project join programmes as t3 on t3.code=t2.programme join projects as t4 on t4.unics_id=t1.project where t1.region_name='Toscana' and t4.framework_program='H2020'
